 partly owing to the fact that Navajo is a unique language (not similar to basically any others, especially English), and is relatively complex as well), the younger generations struggle to stay engaged. Hopefully more online resources will be available in the future, helping to preserving the language.%0a> %0a> References:%0a> https://www.lakepowelllife.com/a-language-revolution-on-the-navajo-nation/#:~:text=In%25201990%2520the%2520study%2520found,speakers%2520plummeted%2520to%252051%252Dpercent%0a> https://navajotimes.com/reznews/data-shows-huge-reduction-in-dine-speakers/%0a> https://ais.arizona.edu/thesis/revitalization-navajo-language-and-culture%0a> https://www.ethnologue.com/size-and-vitality/nav%0a> https://www.prweb.com/releases/cgtn_america_the_disappearing_language_of_navajo/prweb17973961.htm%0a
